body:
Just updated to 4.18.0 and we ran into this issue when calling `fromPairs`. Rolling back to 4.17.21 and I'm good. 


```
import fromPairs from 'lodash/fromPairs';

const ITEM_CATEGORIES = {
  electronics: { title: 'Electronics', id: 1 },
  clothing: { title: 'Clothing', id: 2 },
  furniture: { title: 'Furniture', id: 3 },
};

const categoryTitles = fromPairs(
  Object.keys(ITEM_CATEGORIES).map(key => [key, ITEM_CATEGORIES[key].title]),
);
```

Anyone else running into this issue?

## Reproduction
```JS
function halloWelt(){
  console.log('Hallo Welt')
}

var directClone = _.cloneDeep(halloWelt);
var indirectClone = _.cloneDeep({
  result: halloWelt
}).result;

console.log('isEqual:', _.isEqual(directClone, indirectClone)); // isEqual: false
console.log('directClone:', directClone); // directClone: {}
console.log('indirectClone:', indirectClone); // indirectClone: function halloWelt()
```

## Expected
The `isEqual` should return `true`.

## Actually
`false` is returned. Th

Example:

```js
const _ = require('lodash');
Object.freeze(Object.prototype);

const orig = {
  foo: "bar",
  hasOwnProperty: "a string"
};

console.log(orig.hasOwnProperty); // Output: "a string"

const cloned = _.clone(orig);
console.log(cloned.hasOwnProperty); // Output: "[Function: hasOwnProperty]", expected: "a string"

const spreadCopy = { ...orig };
console.log(spreadCopy.hasOwnProperty); // Output: "a string"
```

`cloneDeep()` demonstrates the same behavior.

