There seems to be a bug with how negative numbers are rounded.

The solution used for rounding numbers in Lodash seems pretty good for positive numbers, but when e.g. trying to round `-1.005` to 2 decimals the result is `-1` when it should be `-1.01`

A solution like this should fix this issue:

```js
function round (number, precision = 2) {
    return Math.sign(number) * Number(`${Math.round(`${Math.abs(number)}e+${precision}`)}e-${precision}`);
}
```

