## Description
I've noticed that the `_.isEqual` method incorrectly evaluates objects with circular references as equal. This behavior can lead to unexpected results, especially when dealing with complex data structures.

## Reproduction
Here is a simple code snippet to reproduce the issue:

```javascript
const lodash = require('lodash');

const a = {};
a.self = a;

const b = {};
b.self = b;

console.log(lodash.isEqual(a, b));  // Outputs: true

