This is the same issue that was reported and auto-closed without resolution in #3703:

```js
const source = { a: ['foo'] };

_.unset(source, 'a[0]');

console.log(source); // { a: [empty] }

console.log(source.a.length); // 1
```

The behaviour does match the util's name, but unset's documentation claims the item is removed; overwriting is not removing.

`_.omit` suffers the same issue, but the name also suggests the array should be compacted.

