The #️⃣ emoji is composed of (like the other keycap emojis):
- a starting symbol, in this case `#`
- a `\uFE0F` variation selector
- a combining enclosing keycap `\u20E3`

`_.toArray` on a #️⃣ emoji returns an array of length two, with the first two items in index 0 and the combining enclosing keycap in index 1.

``` js
var _ = require('lodash');

console.log(_.toArray('5️⃣'));
//= [ '5️', '⃣' ]
console.log(_.toArray('#️⃣'));
//= [ '#️', '⃣' ]
console.log(_.toArray('*⃣'));
//= [ '*', '⃣' ]
```

