There's an inconsistency with Lo-Dash and Underscore:

``` javascript
var sorted = _.sortBy({ 
    a: { prop: 2 }, 
    b: { prop: 1 } 
  }, function (obj) {
    return obj.prop;
  });

console.log(sorted); 

// Lo-Dash output: [undefined]

// Underscore output: [ { prop: 1 }, { prop: 2 } ]
```

Underscore's behavior is extremely useful.  I use this [in Rekapi](https://github.com/jeremyckahn/rekapi/blob/master/ext/canvas/rekapi.canvas.context.js#L47), for example.

Before:

``` js
// Up front
var toString = Object.prototype.toString;

// 21 times thereafter
toString.call(value)
```

After:

``` js
// Up front
var toString = _.bind(Function.call, Object.prototype.toString);

// 21 times thereafter
toString(value)
```

